config SENTRAOS_RUSTCORE
	bool "SentraOS Rust Core — rewrite kernel core in Rust"
	depends on RUST
	help
	  Replaces legacy C kernel subsystems with modern Rust implementations:
	    - panic handler (detailed box-art explanations)
	    - scheduler (EEVDF, lockless per-CPU runqueues)
	    - process manager (fork/exit/signal with sandbox tracking)
	    - boot logger (structured startup/shutdown output)
	    - calls dispatch (modern syscall replacement)
	    - VFS (capability-based FD passing)
	    - memory manager (per-sandbox budgets, lockless allocator)

	  These modules compile alongside the existing C code.  The C code
	  is bypassed at runtime when the Rust version is loaded.

	  If unsure, say N.

config SENTRAOS_OOM_RUST
	bool "SentraOS OOM Killer — ML-like context-aware scoring"
	depends on SENTRAOS_RUSTCORE
	help
	  Replaces the legacy OOM killer heuristic (mm/oom_kill.c) with a
	  15-factor weighted scoring model that considers sandbox priority,
	  cgroup context, interactivity, memory growth rate, CPU time,
	  DMA allocations, and more.  Provides OOM immunity to prevent
	  repeated killing of the same process, per-sandbox OOM priorities,
	  and full decision logging.

	  If unsure, say N.

config SENTRAOS_SIGNAL_RUST
	bool "SentraOS Signal Manager — race-free, thread-aware signals"
	depends on SENTRAOS_RUSTCORE
	help
	  Replaces the legacy kernel/signal.c delivery path (~4900 lines)
	  with a clean design:
	    - Lockless pending queues (atomic bitmask per thread)
	    - Thread-aware delivery (target specific thread or whole group)
	    - Async-safe exit handling (no use-after-free races)
	    - No raw sigset_t manipulation — safe atomic operations
	    - Per-sandbox signal accounting

	  Key entry points (do_send_sig_info, force_sig_info_to_task,
	  dequeue_signal, flush_signals) redirect to the Rust manager
	  when this is enabled.  The legacy C code remains untouched.

	  If unsure, say N.
